author: Curtis Rockwell
title: East Central beats Moss Point in football for the first time in history | gulflive.com
text:
Coming into Friday nights game against visiting Moss Point, East Central was 0-6 all time on the gridiron against the once perennial power Tigers.
But Hornet senior standout tailback A. J. Davis made sure that streak wouldn't reach seven.
Davis ran for over 300 yards and three touchdowns, including one with just under three minutes to play that sealed the deal, as the homestanding Hornets knocked off Moss Point 34-21 at Shirley Stadium.
The game served as the Region 8-4A opener for both squads, as the Hornets over to 4-2 overall and Moss Point dropped to 3-3.
This story will be updated.
